modules.description: This module implements low-level Ethernet I/O operations for network device interaction, including packet transmission and reception, MAC address and MTU access, and statistics tracking. It operates on network interface handles (`t`), Ethernet frames (`Cstruct.t` buffers), and packet metadata like MAC addresses (`Macaddr.t`). Concrete use cases include sending raw Ethernet frames, receiving packets with custom handlers, retrieving interface statistics, and managing connection lifecycle events.
